OL,3,C'Grief will not define' soldier's
OL,4,Cparents as they launch anti-bullying
OL,5,Ccampaign
OL,7,F"When we do have our down moments, we
OL,8,Fsay, 'what would Callum do?' because
OL,9,Fhe has inspired us so much.
OL,11,F"He had so many down moments as a
OL,12,Fteenager. And yet he picked himself up
OL,13,Fand he carried on. And that's what we
OL,14,Fare doing.
OL,16,F"Callum will always be part of our
OL,17,Ffamily, he's always going to be the
OL,18,Feldest brother, the eldest son. But
OL,19,Fit's important to recognise that we do
OL,20,Fhave three other children and we are
OL,21,Fthere for them."
